---

Peel the @red onion{2}(peeled and thinly sliced widthways into half moons) and chop your @garlic clove{2}(peeled and chopped). Remove the core from your @red pepper{2}(cored and sliced into strips) and slice into strips. Cut your @vine tomatoes{2}(cut into quarters and chopped into four) in half, then into quarters and then chop each quarter into four. Remove your leaves from your @oregano{5%sprigs}(leaves removed and roughly chopped) and roughly chop them.

Bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Put your @brown basmati rice{2} in a #sieve{} (if you have one) and run water through it for at least ~{30%seconds}. Once the water is boiling, add the rice to the pot and cook on a rapid boil for ~{25%minutes}. When the rice is cooked, drain, take off the heat, cover with a #tea towel{} and leave until everything else is ready.

> If the rice dries out before it's cooked just add a bit more water!

> If the rice is ready before everything else, don't worry... it will wait!

Add @olive oil{2%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook for ~{3%minutes}. Add the @cumin{1/2} and cook for another ~{3%minutes}.

While your onion and garlic is cooking, cut up your @British chicken thighs{6}(cut into 3cm pieces) and when the onion and garlic has softened (after ~{6%minutes}) add the chicken to the #pan{}. Cook for about ~{4%minutes} making sure the outside of the chicken pieces are cooked.

> You don't have to completely cook your chicken at this stage.

Add the @chipotle paste{2} to the pan with the chicken along with the pepper, chopped tomato and chopped oregano leaves. Stir together and cook for about ~{3%minutes} until everything has softened a little.

Drain the @organic black beans{2}, put them in a sieve and run some cold water through them to rinse them. Add the beans to the chicken pan along with your @chicken stock pot{1} and @water{350%ml}. Simmer on a low heat uncovered for ~{15%minutes} until it thickens up and the vegetables are soft.

> Stir occasionally to stop it sticking to the bottom of the pan.

Roughly chop your @coriander{4}(roughly chopped) and have a quick kitchen tidy while everything is cooking!

When everything is ready serve the rice with the stew on top, a dollop of @sour cream{1} and a sprinkling of coriander.